<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,544,1111]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, W. J." box="[280,408,544,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4500" refString="Fox, W. J. (1893) Report on some Mexican Hymenoptera, principally from Lower California. Transactions of the California Academy of Sciences, 2, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1893">Fox (1893)</bibRefCitation>
based the description of this species on an undetermined number of females collected in Guaymas, 
<collectingRegion box="[271,416,580,607]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Sinaloa state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[427,516,580,606]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[527,747,580,607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref5052" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[609,658,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned a type series composed by at least four specimens housed at 
<collectionCode box="[265,323,616,642]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" type="Museum">CAS</collectionCode>
. Two females were found at 
<collectionCode box="[643,714,616,642]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">ANSP</collectionCode>
that agree with the information provided in the original description being both certainly primary types. One of these specimens has a red label with the words “Type 
<date box="[1293,1379,652,678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" value="91-10-11">101191</date>
” and the other one has a light green label with the words “Para-type 
<date box="[841,930,688,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" value="91-10-11">101191</date>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, W. J." box="[949,1073,688,715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4500" refString="Fox, W. J. (1893) Report on some Mexican Hymenoptera, principally from Lower California. Transactions of the California Academy of Sciences, 2, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1893">Fox (1893)</bibRefCitation>
did not indicate explicitly which female was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[492,594,724,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">holotype</typeStatus>
; therefore, a 
<typeStatus box="[745,848,724,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">lectotype</typeStatus>
needs to be designated. The specimen labeled with the word “type” is in better condition, and it is here designated 
<typeStatus box="[872,978,760,786]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The chosen specimen has the following data label (
<figureCitation box="[275,344,795,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 and 6" captionStartId="3.[151,275,1913,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1358,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1358,1893]" captionText="FIGURES 5 and 6. Labels. Fig. 5: Centris eisenii Fox, 1893 (lectotype female). Fig. 6: Centris errans Fox, 1899 (lectotype female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3430110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3430110/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): [light brown label] Guaymas Mex [handwritten]\ [light brown label] 
<taxonomicName authority="Fox" authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1893" box="[1142,1356,797,823]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eisenii">
<emphasis box="[1142,1305,797,823]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Centris eisenii</emphasis>
Fox
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]\ [white label] 1980 Loan to 
<collectionCode box="[562,643,832,858]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
from Acad. of Nat. Sciences at Philadelphia [printed]\ [dark red label] Type No. [printed] 10191 [handwritten]\ [light blue label] 
<typeStatus box="[804,916,869,895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Lectotype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Fox, 1893 F. Vivallo" authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1893" box="[923,1322,868,895]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eisenii">
<emphasis box="[923,1085,869,895]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Centris eisenii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, W. J." box="[1093,1206,868,895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4500" refString="Fox, W. J. (1893) Report on some Mexican Hymenoptera, principally from Lower California. Transactions of the California Academy of Sciences, 2, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1893">Fox, 1893</bibRefCitation>
F. Vivallo
</taxonomicName>
des, 2017 [handwritten]. 
<typeStatus box="[317,469,904,930]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
female with the following data label: [light brown label] Guaymas Mex [handwritten]\ [light pink label] 
<taxonomicName authority="Fox" authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1893" box="[354,572,941,967]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eisenii">
<emphasis box="[354,518,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Centris eisenii</emphasis>
Fox
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]\ [light green label] Para-Type [printed] 10191 [handwritten]\ [light blue label] 
<typeStatus box="[347,499,976,1002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Fox, 1893 F. Vivallo" authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1893" box="[507,910,976,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eisenii">
<emphasis box="[507,671,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">Centris eisenii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, W. J." box="[678,793,976,1003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4500" refString="Fox, W. J. (1893) Report on some Mexican Hymenoptera, principally from Lower California. Transactions of the California Academy of Sciences, 2, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1893">Fox, 1893</bibRefCitation>
F. Vivallo
</taxonomicName>
des, 2017 [handwritten]. Both type specimens are in good condition. The presence of 
<typeStatus box="[589,687,1013,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">syntypes</typeStatus>
(now 
<typeStatus box="[759,923,1012,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="480">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
) at 
<collectionCode box="[964,1018,1012,1038]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="2" pageNumber="480" type="Museum">CAS</collectionCode>
could not be confirmed.
</paragraph>
